---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import ImageWarp from "@/components/ImageWarp.svelte";
---

<BaseLayout title="Me — Abdulla AlBassam">
  <div class="page">
    <div class="page-header">
      <h1>ABOUT ME</h1>
    </div>

    <div class="about-layout">
      <div class="about-content">
        <div class="bio">
          <p>
            I'm Abdulla AlBassam, a final-year Cybersecurity and Networking
            student at Northumbria University, on track for a First Class
            Honours degree. I'm a recipient of the Saudi government's "Emdad"
            Scholarship (The Custodian of the Two Holy Mosques Scholarship
            Program), and I hold the Cisco CCNA and ISC2 CC certifications,
            with the eJPT currently in progress and the OSCP on my longer-term
            roadmap.
          </p>
          <p>
            My final year computing project sits at the intersection of machine
            learning and cybersecurity. I am building an adversarially robust
            spam detection system using a fine-tuned DistilBERT transformer
            model deployed within a secure mail server pipeline, evaluating how
            intelligent systems can be hardened against adversarial
            manipulation. That project represents the kind of work I find most
            compelling, where deep technical problems meet real-world security
            threats.
          </p>
          <p>
            Across my degree, I've worked hands-on in penetration testing,
            defensive security, enterprise networking, digital forensics, and
            secure software architecture. I've conducted vulnerability
            assessments using Nmap and Burp Suite, implemented defensive
            controls with iptables and Snort, designed a multi-site enterprise
            WAN with MPLS VPN and IPSec in GNS3, carried out forensic
            investigations using Autopsy, FTK Imager, and Volatility 3, and
            built a secure REST API from scratch. Outside of university, I
            sharpen my offensive skills through CTF challenges on TryHackMe and
            Hack The Box, working through real-world exploitation and privilege
            escalation scenarios.
          </p>
          <p>
            I also build things on the side. I founded Sweaty, a social
            platform for gamers that I designed and developed end-to-end using
            React Native. It features reviews, ratings, curated lists, a
            real-time social feed, AI-powered recommendations, and
            game-library importing. The app is currently in pilot testing
            before its full public release. Teaching myself full-stack mobile
            development, database design, and UI/UX principles from scratch to
            bring a product to life taught me invaluable skills in the realm of
            how business is conducted in the real world, and I look forward to
            further developing my computing skills, no matter the niche.
          </p>
          <p>
            I'm a member of the Claude Builder Club at Northumbria, where I
            work on agentic AI development and automation projects. I've also
            completed certifications from Anthropic and Google in AI
            prototyping and agentic development. Whether it's security,
            software, or AI, I'm drawn to building things that work, breaking
            things that don't, and understanding the theory behind both.
          </p>
          <p>
            Contact me <a href="/contact" class="bio-link">here</a>, or find my
            <a href="https://letterboxd.com/3boodi/" class="bio-link">Letterboxd</a> :)
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="education">
          <h2>EDUCATION</h2>
          <div class="edu-card">
            <span class="period">2023 — 2026</span>
            <h3>BSc (Honours) Networks &amp; Cyber Security</h3>
            <p class="institution">Northumbria University, Newcastle</p>
            <p class="institution">Predicted grade: 1st Class Honours</p>
            <p class="description">
              Studying network architecture, ethical hacking, digital forensics,
              and security operations. Hands-on labs in penetration testing and
              incident response.
            </p>
            <div class="modules">
              <span>Network Security</span>
              <span>Ethical Hacking</span>
              <span>Digital Forensics</span>
              <span>Cryptography</span>
              <span>Operating Systems</span>
              <span>Routing &amp; Switching</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="edu-card">
            <span class="period">2022 — 2023</span>
            <h3>Foundation Year — Economics &amp; Mathematics</h3>
            <p class="institution">King's College London</p>
            <p class="institution">Grade: 2:1</p>
            <p class="description">
              Combined economics and mathematics, covering essential mathematical
              topics for university-level business and economics study. The Economics
              module explored macroeconomics and microeconomics, examining how
              economic and social environments influence government and
              organisational decision-making.
            </p>
            <div class="modules">
              <span>Economics</span>
              <span>Mathematics</span>
              <span>Business &amp; Society</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="edu-card">
            <span class="period">2008 — 2022</span>
            <h3>American Diploma with Honours</h3>
            <p class="institution">Modern Knowledge Schools, Manama, Bahrain</p>
            <p class="institution">98% Overall GPA</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="photo-area">
        <img src="/aboutme.jpg" alt="Abdulla AlBassam" class="photo" />
        <ImageWarp client:visible />
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page {
    min-height: 100vh;
    padding: 8rem 2rem 4rem;
    max-width: 1000px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .page-header h1 {
    font-family: "Space Grotesk", sans-serif;
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 5rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    color: white;
    margin: 0 0 3rem 0;
  }

  .about-layout {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 280px;
    gap: 4rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .bio p {
    color: #999;
    line-height: 1.8;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem 0;
  }

  .bio-link {
    color: #ccc;
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .bio-link:hover {
    color: white;
  }

  .education {
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }

  .education h2 {
    font-family: "Space Grotesk", sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #555;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem 0;
  }

  .edu-card {
    border: 1px solid #1a1a1a;
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    transition: border-color 0.3s;
  }

  .edu-card:hover {
    border-color: #2a2a2a;
  }

  .period {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: #555;
    font-family: "Space Grotesk", sans-serif;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  .edu-card h3 {
    font-family: "Space Grotesk", sans-serif;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: white;
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0 0;
  }

  .institution {
    color: #666;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    margin: 0.25rem 0 0 0;
  }

  .description {
    color: #888;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 1rem 0 0 0;
  }

  .modules {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .modules span {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03);
    border: 1px solid #1a1a1a;
    border-radius: 999px;
    color: #777;
  }

  .photo-area {
    position: sticky;
    top: 8rem;
    overflow: hidden;
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    border: 1px solid #1a1a1a;
  }

  .photo {
    width: 100%;
    aspect-ratio: 3 / 4;
    object-fit: cover;
    display: block;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .page {
      padding: 7rem 1.5rem 3rem;
    }

    .about-layout {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 2rem;
    }

    .photo-area {
      order: -1;
      position: static;
    }

    .photo-area {
      max-width: 200px;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }

    .photo {
      aspect-ratio: 1;
    }
  }
</style>
